description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job title:&lt;/strong&gt; Biomedical Scientist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Romford&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt; £31,365 - £40,000 depending on experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours:&lt;/strong&gt; 37.5 hours per week, Monday to Friday&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Biomedical Scientist&lt;/strong&gt; to join our community health clinic in &lt;strong&gt;Romford&lt;/strong&gt;. The clinic houses a histopathology laboratory and utilises a digital pathology platform to produce the highest quality results with fast turnaround times. The state-of-the-art equipment and advanced, modern surroundings contribute to an excellent working environment for staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will being aBiomedical Scientistwith us involve?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will undertake routine and complex laboratory procedures in the processing of diagnostic histology samples to provide patients with the highest level of diagnosis within agreed quality standards of service delivery and turnaround times. You will apply skill, knowledge, accuracy and dexterity to perform a variety of technical procedures that include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sample transfer and basic tissue dissection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tissue processing and embedding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tissue microtomy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Special stains (Immunostaining TBC)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as part of a small team and deputise for the Pathology Manager in their absence, taking responsibility of the department, as required.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;What skills and experience will you need to apply?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Theoretical knowledge and practical experience of biomedical procedures – this will have been gained through BSc or equivalent degree, and consolidated by the completion of an IBMS specialist diploma or equivalent in Cellular Pathology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional membership registration (HCPC)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Quality Management Systems, Quality Assurance and Laboratory accreditation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sound understanding of Health and Safety&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of Word and Excel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why should you consider working with InHealth?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer you the opportunity to do something you love, with the right support to access the roles you want, through clear career paths and best-in-class training and development. This is an environment where you have accountability for your career and are able to make a real contribution to the organisation and to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s in it for you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A highly competitive salary is a given, topped with a generous flexible benefits package, including private medical insurance, excellent holiday allowance, company pension and many more discounts.We also offer an innovative approach to personal and professional development, helping you to be the best version of you and giving you a real career pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;InHealth is an equal opportunities employer and welcomes applications from all areas of the community.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
